Author: snos-boss
Title: [ANN]ğŸ¢ACCOUNTING BLOCKCHAINğŸ¢ Linking business accounts through blockchain
Body: The immediate benefit to those business that would start using AB Fingertips Suite is the reduction in the accountantsâ€™ time required. Many firms would immediately drastically reduce the number of accountants employed in reconciliation departments. Auditing time required will be reduced drastically due to the fact that audit tests performed would no longer need to check the validity of the triple entry transactions. These are being confirmed by the other company on the opposing spectrum, which is an independent 3rd party. Auditors will start placing reliance on Triple Entries as they are cemented in the Blockchain. Throughout the consultation stage, AB encountered many businesses explaining how rogue employees within their organisation used creative accounting and manipulation of data to defraud their employer. This in the past has been as easy as changing the supplier invoice bank details in order to channel the funds their way. Currently to deter this type of fraud and other fraud risks, companies undertake to implement flimsy, costly and time consuming systems of internal control, including multiple checking and re-checking. ABâ€™s Fingertips Triple Entry Suite will serve as a shield against fraud as invoice details as well as the suppliersâ€™ bank details as well as all invoice data would be recorded in the Blockchain and can never be manipulated. (WP)

Author: accountingblockchain
Title: [ANN]ğŸ¢ACCOUNTING BLOCKCHAINğŸ¢ Linking business accounts through blockchain
Body: Hi Noruka, thank you very much for your feedback, Paypie have a great concept, however it on a different business model than Acccounting Blockchain. Accounting Blockchain focuses on solutions connecting businesses' accounting process through amongst others  triple entry accounting thus reducing the need for duplication of work and reconciliations. Invoice factoring (the kind offerred by paypie) also stands to gain from this type of connections between businesses that do not necessarily use the same accounting software. AB is also providing solutions for smart contract integration and crypto currency integration in the day to day operations of businesses  from the small shop to the multinational corporations. Another platform AB is offering is AB Taxavance which is a platform that incorporates tracking of transactions to tax parameters. Again thanks a lot for the interest and hope this answers your question

Author: accountingblockchain
Title: [ANN]ğŸ¢ACCOUNTING BLOCKCHAINğŸ¢ Linking business accounts through blockchain
Body: Blockchain technology is based on ledgers. Similarly, all accounting data is based on ledgers. At accounting blockchain, we will be using Blockchain technology in order to link business accounting together and drive away inefficiencies which currently clutter the system.  Quote Blockchain has the potential to enhance the accounting profession by reducing the costs of maintaining and reconciling ledgers, and providing absolute certainty over the ownership and history of assets. Blockchain could help accountants gain clarity over the available resources and obligations of their organisations, and also free up resources to concentrate on planning and valuation, rather than recordkeeping.  Blockchain is a replacement for bookkeeping and reconciliation work. This could threaten the work of accountants in those areas, while adding strength to those focused on providing value elsewhere.- ICAEW  Here's the direct link to the ICAEW article written independently from Accounting Blockchain

Author: accountingblockchain
Title: [ANN]ğŸ¢ACCOUNTING BLOCKCHAINğŸ¢ Linking business accounts through blockchain
Body: Hello,  Accounting Blockchain will be delivering 3 different products: -  1.The Accounting Blockchain 2.AB Fingertips Suite 3.AB Taxavance  1. THE ACCOUNTING BLOCKCHAIN  The Problem Accounting data is very sensitive and needs to be stored in a secure, trustworthy place. More so when this data involves multiple parties, the data needs to be stored in a secure place that is trusted by all parties. Mutability, malicious attacks, transactions costs, scams, lack of assurance of authenticity have all been barriers in providing a trusted common ground to store B2B entries that can be trusted by all parties. Thus the status quo prevails, and companies remain operating in relative isolation accounting-wise spending billions in reconciliation costs.  The Solution A trusted, secure common ground where to store triple entry information is the key to connecting businesses though triple entries. The Accounting Blockchain - a tailor made blockchain infrastructure built specifically for accounting and for triple entries. A platform available for everyone to be able to use without having to pay hefty subscription fees to any particular software company. A distributed, trustworthy, fast, secure common ground where businesses feel confident to connect with. This is only possible with the advancements in Blockchain technology.  2. AB FINGERTIPS SUITE  The Problem Reconciliation of transactions between companies is a multibillion dollar problem. A small to medium sized company has hundreds/thousands of transactions between its suppliers and its customers, let alone large corporations. Each company must reconcile each and every transaction and the balances due have to be agreed upon. For a small company itâ€™s a nuisance and a waste of valuable time, for a medium sized enterprise its about employing a few accountants for reconciliations with costs running into hundreds of thousands, and for a large corporation itâ€™s about having huge reconciliation departments with hundreds of employees and millions in expenses.  The Solution Introducing a viable way to have triple entries that automatically connect businesses in their transactions. An accounting software platform built around the triple entry concept. A user friendly, really easy to use accounting platform that drastically reduces the costs of reconciliations by using the power and trustworthiness of blockchain to store triple entries. A catalyst in connecting businesses together and in incorporating the much needed blockchain technology into the accounting world.[/color]   AB TAXAVANCE  The Problem Being proactive in tax decisions when making crypto investments is of the utmost importance to any sensible investor. Regulation and enforcement in this sector is gathering pace. Investments and trades are global and subject to a myriad of tax frameworks globally. The tricky part in this is finding all the information needed in one place to make wise decisions fast. Regulations are changing quickly, and it is imperative to have the correct knowledge while and after doing trades. Preparing tax reports and gathering all the information from exchanges is time consuming and very expensive when done manually by a tax accountant.  The Solution A really easy to use platform that keeps track of your trades and their tax implications. A platform with tax parameters fed by a global network of tax experts that is able to work out in real time the tax exposure of your crypto trades and investments. A global network of tax experts and collaborators at your fingertips. Pre-trading information including trade simulations to make proactive decisions. Keeping record of your trades and their current tax exposure should you buy more, hold, or sell. Issuing end-term tax reports of your trades and investments. AI assisted report input that may read reports from exchanges and setting up a common protocol to interface with exchanges. A true global 247 tax assistant.

Author: accountingblockchain
Title: [ANN]ğŸ¢ACCOUNTING BLOCKCHAINğŸ¢ Linking business accounts through blockchain
Body: https://i.imgur.com/jbP0rR7.jpg  Accounting Blockchain - Empowering businesses and individuals with blockchain technology to address a multi-billion dollar yearly problem  "Blockchain technology is the ultimate solution to handle the inefficiencies in the accounting processes faced by businesses globally on a daily basis"  â€“ Nathaniel Borg (CEO)  PUBLIC TOKEN SALE official opening date 15 July 2018 10:00 UCT  â­ï¸ TOP-RATED ICO: ICObench 4.5/5 | ICOmarks 9.3/10 | ICO Track 4.6/5 | FoundICO 8.2/10 | ICO Holder 4.22/5â­ï¸ â­ï¸ 1st ESTS Initiative Competition Winners by public jury â­ï¸  https://i.imgur.com/8Dq9kZ6l.png  Website | Whitepaper |Executive Summary | One Pager | Token Registration | Twitter | Telegram | Reddit | Facebook | Medium  Accounting Inefficiencies and Problem      At the start of a new month, accountants around the world close the books on the prior month. At large companies, this process takes anywhere from a couple of business days to a week or longer. - Eric Rosenberg  The Solution and what 3rd parties have to say to accounting records kept on blockchain technology  The blockchain technology has the potential to shapeshift the nature of today's accounting. It may constitute a way to vastly automate accounting processes in compliance with the regulatory requirements.- Deloitte Direct Link to Deloitte Article   Blockchain has the potential to enhance the accounting profession by reducing the costs of maintaining and reconciling ledgers, and providing absolute certainty over the ownership and history of assets. Blockchain could help accountants gain clarity over the available resources and obligations of their organisations, and also free up resources to concentrate on planning and valuation, rather than recordkeeping.  Blockchain is a replacement for bookkeeping and reconciliation work. This could threaten the work of accountants in those areas, while adding strength to those focused on providing value elsewhere.- ICAEW Direct link to ICAEW   With the distributed Blockchain ledger, there is no need for transactions to sit in limbo. There is no need for a delay in processing while systems catch up and run overnight processes. In a world of instant transactions, many month end close processes will be cut down or eliminated completely. Thanks to to speed transactions will be completed, accountants will spend a lot less time worrying about ensuing transactions are reported in the correct month, as they will already be reported when the month closes. And, once transactions are completed, they are locked in and recorded forever. There is no going back to tinker or adjust past transactions in a blockchain - Eric Rosenberg. Eric Rosenberg   Of all recent innovations that have or will profoundly change the world as we know it, one will be more disruptive than all others: the Blockchain. With the potential to redefine the economic fabric of contemporary society, the Blockchain is an innovation that no business executive can afford to ignore. - Steve Tendon Steve Tendon   And everyone will be wondering, why didnâ€™t I see that coming? I wish I got in back then when everyone was missing the forest for the trees.  Imagine buying shares in the United States when the first settlers got here and swindled the Native Americans out of Manhattan.  What would those shares be worth today? Why Everyone Missed the Most Important Invention in the Last 500 Years  3 Products requiring AB Tokens = 3 times the demand for AB Tokens  1. The Accounting Blockchain (TAB) 2. AB Fingertips Suite 3. AB Taxavance  1. The Accounting Blockchain (TAB)  https://i.imgur.com/7noGnpgl.jpg  Market Size:  - Trillions of B2B and B2C of global transactions yearly. Multiplied by 2, as most of these are currently duplicated due to isolated accounting systemsâ€Šâ€”â€ŠTAB is about to solve this.  Market Penetration:  - Gradual at first due to cultural shift in the way things are done. Author: accountingblockchain
Title: [ANN]ğŸ¢ACCOUNTING BLOCKCHAINğŸ¢ Linking business accounts through blockchain
Body: Couldn't agree more. Businesses who start using blockchain technology in their accounting send the message that they want to be as transparent as possible in order to boost investor confidence. Additional to that, businesses would also benefit from the following: -  1. They would drastically reduce their accountancy fees due to the fact that a large proportion of their accounting records would be automated and recorded on blockchain;  2. Save on audit fees. Auditors spend most of their time obtaining 3rd party supporting evidence to verify the transactions recorded by businesses. With blockchain technology, they will have smart contracts immediately available which come from the 3rd parties and would be able to verify the data immediately;  3. For large businesses, they can easily save money as they would no longer require to employ such a large accounting division since the work is automated;  4. Fraud and creative accounting as was with Enron would become a thing of the past as fraud would be much more difficult;  5. Taxation authorities would know which businesses to trust, those that keep their records on the blockchain as there won't be room for manipulation of records;  6. Small businesses would save their time. Rather than having to record their transactions, the majority would be automated and they would be able to focus more on their business and on their family.  I'm attaching a link to one of the videos which explains some of the many benefits The Accounting Blockchain can provide. Click here for YouTube video

A number of integrations are being developed so that businesses can start paying for each others services using crypto. We are very confident that having a crypto ready payment system integrated in the accounting software will impact many businesses. Businesses will be able to instantly settle payments they owe to each other by paying in AB Tokens, Bitcoin or with other currencies.
